verbose_text: Having established that the BRAF V600E derived neopeptide KIGDFGLATEK can bind to two HLA class I molecules that are relatively frequent in the Caucasian population, we evaluated whether BRAF V600E mutated LCH-patients expressing HLA-A * 03:01 and/or HLA-A * 11:01 had increased event-free survival as compared to LCH-patients without these HLA genotypes.
evidence: BRAF V600E  derived neopeptide KIGDFGLATEK can bind to two HLA class I molecules
